{{Nihongo|'''''Re: Hamatora'''''|Re: ␣ ハマトラ||stylized '''''Re:␣Hamatora''''' and pronounced "Reply Hamatora"}}, is a 2014 supernatural, mystery [[anime]] series based on the Japanese mixed-media project, ''[[Hamatora]]''. It is set in the year 2014 where select humans called Minimum Holders have been discovered to possess supernatural abilities. The series is a direct sequel to ''[[List of Hamatora: The Animation episodes|Hamatora: The Animation]]'' and features the same main cast as the original one. Set three months after the events of ''The Animation'', the story follows Minimum Holders known as Hamatora who solve cases.

The series was produced by [[Lerche (studio)|Lerche]] while [[NAZ (studio)|NAZ]], the studio behind the first series, assisted in the making of it. [[Seiji Kishi]] is directing the series while Jun Kumagi is the main writer. Character designs are done by Yū Wazu, based on the original character designs by ''[[Blood Lad|Blood Lad's]]'' Yūki Kodama along with art direction by Fantasista Utamaro. The project was composed by Yukinori Kitajima. The music is being composed by Makoto Yoshimori.  The series premiered in Japan in July 8, 2014 and finished on September 23, 2014.<ref name="ann">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-04-30/re_hamatora-to-air-in-july-with-anime-studio-lerche|title= Re:_Hamatora to Air in July With Anime Studio Lerche|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=April 30, 2014}}</ref><ref name="onair2"/><ref name="madb">{{cite web
| url=http://mediaarts-db.jp/an/anime_series/18477
| title=Ｒｅ:［* HAMATORA リプライハマトラ
|trans-title=Re: Hamatora
| publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] | work=Media Arts Database
| accessdate=January 9, 2016
| location=Japan | language=Japanese}}
</ref> The series was streamed on [[Crunchyroll]] during its first run.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2014/06/25/crunchyroll-to-stream-re-hamatora-anime|title=Crunchyroll to Stream "Re: Hamatora" Anime|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|accessdate=June 25, 2014}}</ref> Animax UK also licensed the series to stream it on their official website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-07-09/animax-uk-adds-re-hamatora-and-rail-wars/.76482vvv|title=Animax UK Adds Re: Hamatora and Rail Wars|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=October 13, 2014}}</ref>

People who purchased the first two volumes of the ''Hamatora: The Animation'' will receive early entry forms for tickets to attend the ''Hamatora Fes 2014.summer event'' which will screen exclusive special footage of the series' sequel, ''Re:␣Hamatora'' at the Pacifico Yokohama on July 13, 2014.<ref name="ann"/> The series is set to start collection in Blu-ray and DVD volumes on September 26, 2014.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://hamatorapj.com/reply/discography/index.php|title=Re：␣ハマトラ 1|publisher=Hamatora PJ|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The series uses two types of musical themes: an opening and an ending theme. The opening theme, {{nihongo|"Sen no Tsubasa"|千の翼||lit. "A Thousand Wings"}} is performed by the collaborative unit of Livetune adding Takuro Sugawara (from 9mm Parabellum Bullet) while Ayami, the voice of ''Hamatora''{{'}}s Chiyū, performs the ending theme, "Brand New World."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-06-23/re-hamatora-anime-1st-full-promo-previews-story-theme-songs/.75842|title= Re:␣Hamatora Anime's 1st Full Promo Previews Story, Theme Songs|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=June 23, 2014}}</ref> 
